<TITLE> Parjatan to transfer 11 tourist facilities to private operators </TITLE>
<TEXT>
 Dhaka, Aug 19 (bdnews24.com)  Bangladesh Parjatan Corporation (BPC) has moved to appoint private operators to manage 11 of its tourist facilities, an official said Sunday. BPC sources said the concerns involved in the move were constant losses. Slated for private management are Parjatan motels in Benapole and Khagrachhari. The Rangamati Tourist Complex will also see four cottages as well as their bar and auditorium in private hands. Also included in the move are Holiday Homes in Kuakata, Hotel Natong in Teknaf and Hotel Madhumoti in Tungipara. Merry Anderson, a floating restaurant at Pagla, will shift to private hands as will the Parjatan Restaurant in Madhabkundo Holiday Complex in Sagardari. Tenders have been floated by the tourism authority. BPC executive officer (planning) Ziaul Haque Howlader told bdnews24.com that bidders would have to turn in 'tender schedules' to BPC by Sept 10. bdnews2
